e to shoaling and wind-forced laboratory\nobservations, suggesting that the vKdV-B equation captures the essential\naspects of wind-induced effects on shoaling wave shape. Finally, we isolate the\nwind's effect by comparing the wave profiles to the unforced case. This reveals\nthat the numerical results are approximately a superposition of a solitary\nwave, a shoaling-induced shelf, and a wind-induced, bound, dispersive, and\ndecaying tail.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Oct 2021 18:01:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 Mar 2022 19:02:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 18:02:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-15"}
