 later $T$-types. We show that the inner\nslope of the RC is coupled with the central surface stellar mass density, which\nimplies that the gravitational potential of central regions of galaxies is\ndominated by baryonic matter. With the aid of simple models for matter\ndistribution, we discuss what determines the shapes of RCs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Oct 2021 14:29:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-15"}
